<subSubSection lastPageId="103" lastPageNumber="104" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="102.[151,1436,1545,2038]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1617,1642]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Description.</emphasis>
Finger-shaped sponges (
<figureCitation box="[639,727,1617,1642]" captionStart="FIGURE 63" captionStartId="102.[151,250,1423,1445]" captionTargetBox="[153,1438,373,1407]" captionTargetId="figure@102.[153,1438,373,1407]" captionTargetPageId="102" captionText="FIGURE 63. Discodermia dissoluta Schmidt, 1880, a, habitus of RMNH 9787 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, SEM image of desma skeleton, c – g, SEM images of spicules, c, oxeote, c 1, details of c, d, discotriaenes, e, large acanthomicroxea, f, middle-sized acanthomicroxea, g, microrhabd, g 1, enlarged image of g." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273014/files/figure.png" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
a), solitary or in a group of three, partially overgrown with hydroids, with dark-brown color in alcohol (possibly darkened by other sponges with aerophobic properties in the same sample haul), up to 
<quantity box="[437,492,1690,1714]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" unit="cm" value="4.0">4 cm</quantity>
high and 
<quantity box="[603,680,1689,1714]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" unit="cm" value="1.5">1.5 cm</quantity>
in diameter. Consistency firm to hard.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="102.[151,1436,1545,2038]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,1725,1750]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Skeleton.</emphasis>
At the surface there is a closed cover of overlapping discotriaenes, carried by occasional perpendicular bundles of oxeas, and overlying a rather open desma network (
<figureCitation box="[1015,1097,1761,1786]" captionStart="FIGURE 63" captionStartId="102.[151,250,1423,1445]" captionTargetBox="[153,1438,373,1407]" captionTargetId="figure@102.[153,1438,373,1407]" captionTargetPageId="102" captionText="FIGURE 63. Discodermia dissoluta Schmidt, 1880, a, habitus of RMNH 9787 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, SEM image of desma skeleton, c – g, SEM images of spicules, c, oxeote, c 1, details of c, d, discotriaenes, e, large acanthomicroxea, f, middle-sized acanthomicroxea, g, microrhabd, g 1, enlarged image of g." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273014/files/figure.png" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="102.[151,1436,1545,2038]" box="[199,1372,1797,1822]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,304,1797,1822]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Spicules.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[319,403,1797,1822]" captionStart="FIGURE 63" captionStartId="102.[151,250,1423,1445]" captionTargetBox="[153,1438,373,1407]" captionTargetId="figure@102.[153,1438,373,1407]" captionTargetPageId="102" captionText="FIGURE 63. Discodermia dissoluta Schmidt, 1880, a, habitus of RMNH 9787 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, SEM image of desma skeleton, c – g, SEM images of spicules, c, oxeote, c 1, details of c, d, discotriaenes, e, large acanthomicroxea, f, middle-sized acanthomicroxea, g, microrhabd, g 1, enlarged image of g." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273014/files/figure.png" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Figs 63</figureCitation>
b–g) Tetraclone desmas, oxeas, discotriaenes, acanthomicroxeas, acanthomicrorhabds.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="102.[151,1436,1545,2038]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
Desmas (
<figureCitation box="[304,385,1833,1858]" captionStart="FIGURE 63" captionStartId="102.[151,250,1423,1445]" captionTargetBox="[153,1438,373,1407]" captionTargetId="figure@102.[153,1438,373,1407]" captionTargetPageId="102" captionText="FIGURE 63. Discodermia dissoluta Schmidt, 1880, a, habitus of RMNH 9787 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, SEM image of desma skeleton, c – g, SEM images of spicules, c, oxeote, c 1, details of c, d, discotriaenes, e, large acanthomicroxea, f, middle-sized acanthomicroxea, g, microrhabd, g 1, enlarged image of g." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273014/files/figure.png" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
b) with smooth shaft and cladi, and strongly tuberculated zygomes, size difficult to measure, approximately 420– 
<emphasis box="[375,417,1870,1894]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">508</emphasis>
–630 µm in overall diameter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="102.[151,1436,1545,2038]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
Oxeas (
<figureCitation box="[293,392,1905,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 63" captionStartId="102.[151,250,1423,1445]" captionTargetBox="[153,1438,373,1407]" captionTargetId="figure@102.[153,1438,373,1407]" captionTargetPageId="102" captionText="FIGURE 63. Discodermia dissoluta Schmidt, 1880, a, habitus of RMNH 9787 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, SEM image of desma skeleton, c – g, SEM images of spicules, c, oxeote, c 1, details of c, d, discotriaenes, e, large acanthomicroxea, f, middle-sized acanthomicroxea, g, microrhabd, g 1, enlarged image of g." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273014/files/figure.png" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Figs 63</figureCitation>
c,c1), usually with bluntly rounded, sometimes even flattened apices, slightly curved, 372– 
<emphasis box="[207,249,1942,1966]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">459</emphasis>
–552 
<date box="[312,345,1941,1966]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">x 5</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[361,396,1942,1966]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">7.8</emphasis>
–11 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="102.[151,1436,1545,2038]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
Discotriaenes (
<figureCitation box="[380,481,1977,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 63" captionStartId="102.[151,250,1423,1445]" captionTargetBox="[153,1438,373,1407]" captionTargetId="figure@102.[153,1438,373,1407]" captionTargetPageId="102" captionText="FIGURE 63. Discodermia dissoluta Schmidt, 1880, a, habitus of RMNH 9787 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, SEM image of desma skeleton, c – g, SEM images of spicules, c, oxeote, c 1, details of c, d, discotriaenes, e, large acanthomicroxea, f, middle-sized acanthomicroxea, g, microrhabd, g 1, enlarged image of g." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273014/files/figure.png" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Figs 63</figureCitation>
d), with slightly concave, rounded or oval, occasionally polyangular discs, characteristically 210– 
<emphasis box="[405,447,2014,2038]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">293</emphasis>
–330 µm in diameter, and conical rhabdomes, 48– 
<emphasis box="[1009,1058,2014,2038]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">74.2</emphasis>
–120 
<date box="[1121,1212,2014,2038]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" value="2010-10-20">x 10–20</date>
µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="103.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">
Acanthomicroxeas (
<figureCitation box="[434,530,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 63" captionStartId="102.[151,250,1423,1445]" captionTargetBox="[153,1438,373,1407]" captionTargetId="figure@102.[153,1438,373,1407]" captionTargetPageId="102" captionText="FIGURE 63. Discodermia dissoluta Schmidt, 1880, a, habitus of RMNH 9787 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, SEM image of desma skeleton, c – g, SEM images of spicules, c, oxeote, c 1, details of c, d, discotriaenes, e, large acanthomicroxea, f, middle-sized acanthomicroxea, g, microrhabd, g 1, enlarged image of g." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273014/files/figure.png" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Figs 63</figureCitation>
e–g), in two categories, (1) larger (
<figureCitation box="[980,1071,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 63" captionStartId="102.[151,250,1423,1445]" captionTargetBox="[153,1438,373,1407]" captionTargetId="figure@102.[153,1438,373,1407]" captionTargetPageId="102" captionText="FIGURE 63. Discodermia dissoluta Schmidt, 1880, a, habitus of RMNH 9787 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, SEM image of desma skeleton, c – g, SEM images of spicules, c, oxeote, c 1, details of c, d, discotriaenes, e, large acanthomicroxea, f, middle-sized acanthomicroxea, g, microrhabd, g 1, enlarged image of g." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273014/files/figure.png" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
e) with sharply pointed ends, 99– 
<emphasis box="[193,231,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">117</emphasis>
–129 
<date box="[296,330,188,212]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">x 4</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[345,380,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">4.3</emphasis>
–4.5 µm, (2) smaller (
<figureCitation box="[625,706,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 63" captionStartId="102.[151,250,1423,1445]" captionTargetBox="[153,1438,373,1407]" captionTargetId="figure@102.[153,1438,373,1407]" captionTargetPageId="102" captionText="FIGURE 63. Discodermia dissoluta Schmidt, 1880, a, habitus of RMNH 9787 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, SEM image of desma skeleton, c – g, SEM images of spicules, c, oxeote, c 1, details of c, d, discotriaenes, e, large acanthomicroxea, f, middle-sized acanthomicroxea, g, microrhabd, g 1, enlarged image of g." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273014/files/figure.png" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
f), also sharply pointed, 38– 
<emphasis box="[1020,1048,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">45</emphasis>
– 
<date box="[1063,1129,188,213]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" value="1951-10-03">51 x 3</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[1145,1180,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">3.7</emphasis>
–4.5 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="103.[151,1437,151,752]" box="[199,1189,223,248]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">
Acanthomicrorhabds (
<figureCitation box="[449,536,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 63" captionStartId="102.[151,250,1423,1445]" captionTargetBox="[153,1438,373,1407]" captionTargetId="figure@102.[153,1438,373,1407]" captionTargetPageId="102" captionText="FIGURE 63. Discodermia dissoluta Schmidt, 1880, a, habitus of RMNH 9787 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, SEM image of desma skeleton, c – g, SEM images of spicules, c, oxeote, c 1, details of c, d, discotriaenes, e, large acanthomicroxea, f, middle-sized acanthomicroxea, g, microrhabd, g 1, enlarged image of g." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273014/files/figure.png" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">
Figs 
<quantity box="[505,536,223,248]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="6.3" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" unit="g" value="63.0">63</quantity>
</figureCitation>
g,g1) with bluntly rounded ends, 13– 
<emphasis box="[948,976,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">17</emphasis>
– 
<date box="[991,1058,224,248]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" value="1919-10-03">19 x 3</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[1074,1109,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">3.4</emphasis>
–4 µm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="103" pageNumber="104" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="103.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,494,260,285]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
